## Test 1 - App loads and displays main content [sanity]
Viewport: desktop
Description: Verifies the app loads correctly on desktop.

Steps:
1. Navigate to the app
2. Wait for page to fully load

Expected: Main heading and navigation are visible."}],"format":["Single file: tests/tests.txt","File starts with '# Tests' header","Each test: '## Test N - <name> [sanity]' (exactly one test gets [sanity])","Required sections per test: Viewport, Description, Steps, Expected","Optional section: Cleanup (reset state after test)"],"rules":["Create your own tests/tests.txt following the exact format shown in tests/example_tests.txt.","NEW APPS: Write 3-10 tests BEFORE implementation code.","Exactly ONE test must be marked [sanity] - pick the test with best balance of coverage and simplicity.","Order tests for stable runtime: fastest high-signal checks first, deeper CRUD/workflow checks second, slower edge/responsive checks last.","[sanity] should be the fastest critical smoke test (app loads + one core interaction + clear visible assertion).","Keep each test concise: prefer 3-6 steps with one primary goal; split multi-goal scenarios into separate tests.","Minimize repeated expensive setup in early tests (auth, refresh, long waits) unless that specific behavior is being tested.","Prefer deterministic expected outcomes anchored to visible UI state; avoid brittle copy-sensitive or timing-fragile assertions.","Design for comprehensive coverage across the full suite: include load/access, core success workflow, state mutation behavior, and failure/guardrail behavior.","Include at least one negative/guardrail test (validation error, permission boundary, empty/error state, or destructive confirmation).","If the app uses authentication, include pre-auth and post-auth expectations and private-data visibility boundaries.","Ensure at least one test checks viewport-specific UX where desktop/mobile behavior can diverge.","Each test must specify viewport: desktop (1280x800) or mobile (375x667).","STATELESS: Each test must work independently. Never assume data from other tests exists.","Use unique identifiers for test data (e.g., include timestamp in emails/names to avoid collisions).","UPDATES: Use diffs[] to modify tests/tests.txt.","UPDATES: When changing user-visible behavior (UI text, elements, workflows, features), update tests/tests.txt via diffs[] to reflect the new behavior. Tests must stay synchronized with the actual app state."]},"deploy_contract":{"rules":["Always include app_id, app_name, app_type, and features (use [] when no SDK features are needed).","New apps require description and frontend_template.","Template files (returned above) are auto-included as the baseline â both for new apps and updates.","Use diffs[] to modify template/existing files. Only use content for entirely new files not in the template.","Do not resend files that haven't changed â they're already in the baseline.","Do not add @appdeploy/client or @appdeploy/sdk to package.json dependencies; the platform injects them.","Frontend must never import @appdeploy/sdk. Backend must never import @appdeploy/client.","SPAs must use HashRouter and avoid absolute client routes.","Frontend must use `import { api } from '@appdeploy/client'` for all backend calls. api.get/post/put/delete work like axios. Never use fetch() or axios directly - api handles auth token injection and base URL routing."],"local_workflow":["Write app files to a local working directory on disk. Use the local tree as the source of truth for all deploy operations.","Use upload_assets to send files to the server â this is the default for all deploys. Only call deploy_app without upload_id for trivially small inline changes (e.g. a one-line fix, a small diff).","Keep metadata such as app_id outside the deploy tree.","For UPDATES, reconstruct the latest snapshot locally with src_glob/src_read before editing."],"upload_workflow":["For apps with binary assets/resources, many files, or an existing local project tree, call upload_assets to get an upload_url and upload_id.","Prefer upload_assets when the source of truth already exists as local files or a local project tree, especially for multiple files or whole-file replacements.","Prepare the local tree and multipart payload first. Call upload_assets only when you can upload immediately.","Binary assets/resources must go through upload_assets. Do not base64-inline images, fonts, media, PDFs, archives, or other binary files into deploy_app.files[].","If the upload_url expires before use, call upload_assets again to get a fresh upload_url and upload_id.","PUT multipart/form-data to the upload_url: a 'payload' part (JSON manifest with text files as content/diffs and deletePaths) plus binary files as separate parts named by their app-relative path. The upload manifest carries all text changes and diffs plus deletePaths.","After upload succeeds, call deploy_app with upload_id only. Do not also send files[] or deletePaths[]; those changes belong in the upload manifest. When you are not using upload_id, deploy_app.files[] is only for inline text file edits."],"status_workflow":{"poll_tool":"get_app_status","retry_after_seconds":5,"terminal_statuses":["ready","failed","deleted"]}},"next_steps":["Scaffold frontend files.","Frontend-only apps can use client-side auth (signIn popup, getUser, signOut) - call get_appdeploy_sdk_reference with features:['auth'] if needed.","Review the returned template + any SDK reference, decide the files/tests/imports you need, then implement locally.","During implementation, report milestones with update_coding_progress({ step, current_task?, note?, app_id? }).","Backend-dependent capabilities (database, storage, realtime, AI, cron) require app_type='frontend+backend'.","If direct HTTP is available and the source already exists as local files or a local project tree, prefer upload_assets for shipping many files or whole-file replacements.","Call deploy_app when ready â pass [] for features unless you explicitly requested SDK features. Poll get_app_status every 5s until status is 'ready' or 'failed'."]}
